Do work that matters:
Retail Banking Services (RBS) Retail Products Credit Risk develops and implements credit strategies for all unsecured retail credit products including Credit Cards, Personal Loans and personal Overdrafts. These strategies span the entire consumer lifecycle from pre-marketing to customer management, including collection of overdue amounts. The team also provides advice and oversight to business teams managing Unsecured Lending.
See yourself in our team
Within this team, Collection Risk Management develops and continually evolves strategies that assist customers facing challenges to fulfil their credit commitments, including collection of overdue repayments or facing financial hardship. The key purpose of this role is to develop and own collection strategies for all retail credit products including Home Loans, Personal Loans and Credit Cards.
In any given week you will be responsible for:
Contributions to the business
Develop and monitor strategies to optimise decisions for the portfolio;
Hypothesis led analytics to understand and assess risk strategy performance, identify opportunities to improve our collection and customer contact strategies and formulate enhancement initiatives using the Group’s Digital Assets;
Generate insight and analysis to understand our existing strategies and formulate new strategies;
Provide timely and accurate advice to key business stakeholders (includes Product, Operations and Risk);
Risk Management
Report, escalate and remediate issues in a timely manner and in line with the Group’s operational risk processes;
Ensure that strategy enhancements remain within the Group’s acceptable risk tolerance levels;
Identify emerging issues with processes and assessment methodologies, work to mitigate / remediate such issues.
Leadership / Management
Work and interact closely with managers and key stakeholders including Operations, Finance, Legal, Risk and Product in monitoring and development of new collections strategies.
We're interested in hearing from people who have:
Experience in SAS / SQL and Excel well regarded with development of these skills necessary for the role ;
Ability to work with large data sets, and understand interactions between relevant data is necessary for the role;
Preferred background in Credit Risk, Analytics, or Data Science with a Financial Services organisation;
Experience in using data manipulation and statistical analysis tools (e.g. SAS, SQL, Tableau) to convert large data sets into easily consumable and insightful reports and business recommendations well regarded;
Ability to use data to derive, justify and implement hypothesis driven strategy optimisation;
Ability in formulating and communicating ideas to management;
Willingness to learn and adhere change management, workflow management, and managing risk to the highest degree of compliance and governance (including documentation);
Your development:
This role will give you the opportunity to understand the largest Retail Bank in Australia from a unique and analytical perspective. You will have the ability to grow within the team, gain exposure to senior management and have access to other roles across Retail Products and Risk Management. You will also benefit from working with our business partners in Product, Analytics, Marketing, Operational Risk, Credit Systems, Compliance, Pricing, and Capital and Provisioning, which will give you the ability to progress your career, whichever path you choose.
If this sounds like the role for you then we would love to hear from you. Apply today!
