The Role
MLCL is undergoing a significant transformation, and therefore, this role will see you in a transition period to strengthen our Data Capabilities and build our data platform target state. This transition requires the integration of different teams. Your skills to navigate the new environment, coordinate, plan, prioritise and resolve conflict are fundamental to team success.
You must thrive in an ambiguous environment that typically accompanies an enterprise going through a large scale multi-year transformation program, and be up for the challenge of creating a new practice within the team. Most specifically, you will be responsible for:
Designing SQL scripts to directly query and analyse internal and external data sources to package together clear, actionable findings for marketing and campaign teams;
Providing timely, valuable solutions for ad hoc analyses via SQL with a focus to detail on crafting scripts that can be easily manipulated to efficiently address similar future analyses;
Working with the data BA, modeller and visualisation engineer to deliver dashboards and KPI reports in PowerBI starting from requirements to the delivery of a final, polished dashboards in production;
Growing to serve as the team's subject matter expert for advanced analytics and report design, offering insights and suggestions on what potential problems the team should be solving;
Working with a variety of data sources - extracting knowledge and actionable information from massive datasets;
Building and fleshing out data models in Customer data mart of the EDW for use in regular and/or automated reporting and analysis;
Being a passionate problem solver - breaking down problems and developing analytical insights;
Conveying your work and results to a wide variety of internal stakeholders;
Diagnosing data-related bugs and ensure they are resolved in a timely manner;
Supporting the marketing and campaign team with ad hoc data analysis and reporting.

